lead_paragraph: In hearing about Fidel Castro’s death, many older Cubans went into mourning, but younger people were generally indifferent.

byline.contributor: Frances Robles contributed reporting from Miami.
byline.original: By DAMIEN CAVE and HANNAH BERKELEY COHEN

headline.print_headline: A Generation Gap in Havana as Sorrow Faces Indifference
headline.main: In Havana, Castro’s Death Lays Bare a Generation Gap

snippet: In hearing about Fidel Castro’s death, many older Cubans went into mourning, but younger people were generally indifferent....
abstract: Death of former Cuban Pres Fidel Castro highlights generation gap, with many older Cubans mourning passing of revolutionary leader while younger citizens regard his passing with indifference; some worry his passing will open rifts inside Cuban government and within global community.
